data.text:
Privately printed for members of the Society of English Bibliophilists, 1901. First Edition. Leather Binding. 8vo - over 7他" - 9他" Very Good / No Jacket. Item #005516175

25 volume set, attractively bound in 3/4 green morocco over marbled boards, spines with raised bands and gilt floral tooling within gilt-bordered compartments, top edges gilt, marbled endpapers (spines faded to brown with some nicking to spine tips). Copy #23 of 100 numbered copies of the Edition De Luxe. 25 volumes, complete as issued. Includes: Paul Clifford; Lucretia, or, The children of night; Ernest Maltravers; Pelham, or, Adventures of a gentleman; Eugene Aram; Alice, or, The mysteries; The last days of Pompeii; Godolphin; Leila, or, The siege of Granada; A strange story; The pilgrims of the Rhine; My novel; The disowned; The Caxtons; a family picture; Devereux; Zanoni; Kenelm Chillingly; his adventures and opinions; Harold; the last of the Saxon kings; The last of the barons; What will he do with it?; Rienzi; the last of the Roman tribunes; Night and morning; The Parisians.B/w Illustrations.
